{
  "answer": "The riverside meditation is found in Allama Iqbal's *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, chapter 28 (\"Kinaar-e-Ravi\").\n\nThe Chughtai-king couplet is:\n\n> Afar they stand, in lonely majesty so deep,[^1]  \n> The minarets of the Chughtai king's last sleep.[^1]\n\nThe closing couplet is:\n\n> It never knows defeat, nor does its journey finish,[^2]  \n> It vanishes from sight, but it does not perish.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/28-kinaar-e-ravi/translation/#p-29acb7).\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/28-kinaar-e-ravi/translation/#p-1c94bb).",
